observations.managementAction:
The Municipal Engineering together with Planning, Accounting and General Service Office will facilitate the necessary actions to comply with this requirement.
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Coordinate with the Inventory Committee in the completion of the inspection, appraisal, and preparation of the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System of the municipality;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Prepare a detailed listing of each road segment, and its condition that provides the necessary details of the road lot;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Provide the municipal accounting office and the general services office with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for each road network;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Update the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant, and Equipment (RPCPPE) incorporating the report furnished by the MEO for accurate tracking;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Maintain detailed Local Road Network Property Card for each road, recording components, acquisition details, condition, maintenance records, and other relevant data;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Generate periodic Local Road Network Report: summarize road network status, including acquisitions, disposals, maintenance, and other updates. Furnish a copy to the accounting office for transparency and accurate reporting.
Municipal Accounting Office (MAO) to record and maintain the local road network: Prepare the Journal Voucher to record and/or adjust the beginning balances of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and individual road cards;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Maintain detailed records: track each road segment and its components separately;
Local Road Asset Management (LRAM) Inventory Committee/ Municipal Engineering Office (MEO)/ Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO)/ Municipal Assessor's Office (MAssO)/ Municipal Treasury Office (MTO)/ Municipal, Accounting Office (MAccO)/ General Services Office (GSO) to: Update the depreciation schedule to ensure accurate computation of the depreciation for every component of the road network; and Effect an adjusting journal entry for the understated depreciation expense and accumulated depreciation for the erroneous provision of residual value.
